llvm-general-pure is a set of pure Haskell types and functions for
interacting with LLVM. It includes an ADT to represent LLVM IR.
The llvm-general package builds on this one with FFI bindings to
LLVM, but llvm-general-pure does not require LLVM to be available.

WWW: http://hackage.haskell.org/package/llvm-general-pure
